<FlowDocument PagePadding="5,0,5,0" AllowDrop="True" xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation">
<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="16">Defining Reports</Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14"><Bold>Reports-in-Code</Bold> - Demonstrates how reports can be defined in code, and how OLAP data can be retrieved and bound to a chart.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14" xml:space="preserve"><Bold>KPI</Bold> - Demonstrates how to view KPI values in an OlapChart.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14"><Bold>MDX Query</Bold> - Essential OlapChart for WPF has the ability to load OLAP data by directly passing the MDX query to the OLAP Data Manager.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14"><Bold>Report-in-File</Bold> - Demonstrates how report files created using the Report Builder utility can be used to initialize a chart.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14"><Bold>XAML Configuration</Bold> - Demonstrates to add an OLAP report created in XAML and bind the data through a XAML configuration.</Paragraph>

</FlowDocument>